<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="runway-calc-how" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">No black box</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2">How cash runway is calculated.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Runway answers one question: at the rate you&rsquo;re spending net of revenue, how long until the cash runs out? The math is <strong>runway in months = cash on hand ÷ average monthly net burn</strong>, where net burn is your monthly expenses minus your monthly revenue. If revenue exceeds expenses, net burn is zero or negative &mdash; you&rsquo;re not burning cash, so there&rsquo;s no runway limit, and the tool says exactly that instead of dividing by zero.</p>
      <p>The hard part isn&rsquo;t the division &mdash; it&rsquo;s getting an honest burn number. Burn should be an average over a few representative months, not your best or worst single month, and it should reflect real cash movements, not accrual timing. That&rsquo;s why accurate books matter: a runway figure built on guesswork is worse than none.</p>
      <p>This is a flat-rate snapshot &mdash; it assumes today&rsquo;s burn holds steady. In reality burn changes with hiring, seasonality, and growth. Use the number as a sanity check, then build a real forward forecast. That&rsquo;s a model of your inputs, not advice.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flow stack-8" role="img" aria-label="From your own numbers, to an instant runway figure, to a free discovery call, to a real cash-flow forecast built on your books.">
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Your own numbers</span><span class="flow__sub">in your browser</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Runway figure</span><span class="flow__sub">instant, honest math</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step flow__step--accent"><span class="flow__label">Free discovery call</span><span class="flow__sub">30 min &middot; no obligation</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">A cash-flow forecast</span><span class="flow__sub">on your real books</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

